57
00:03:52,498 --> 00:03:54,966
who l thought could say it better.

58
00:03:55,368 --> 00:03:56,630
His wife.

59
00:03:57,537 --> 00:03:58,799
Jordan.

60
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:03,676
Well, it ain't breakfast, it's an ambush.

61
00:04:03,776 --> 00:04:06,836
Don't blame Mere. This was my idea.

62
00:04:08,147 --> 00:04:12,413
Anyway, l'm sure you all remember
this weekend is your father's birthday.

63
00:04:13,086 --> 00:04:16,112
<i>And since he's in town for a conference...</i>

64
00:04:16,189 --> 00:04:18,419
l convinced him
to let me throw him a party.

65
00:04:18,491 --> 00:04:19,981
-Yeah.
-Here in his hometown.

66
00:04:20,059 --> 00:04:23,995
And l thought
what could be more special for Richard...

67
00:04:24,063 --> 00:04:26,054
than to spend his birthday with his kids?

68
00:04:26,132 --> 00:04:29,761
-From which marriage?
-Harry, she's trying. Why can't you?

69
00:04:30,603 --> 00:04:33,663
JORDAN: lt's just a small get-together.
TRU: l work nights.

70
00:04:35,508 --> 00:04:38,341
Well, they let you out to eat, don't they?

71
00:04:38,678 --> 00:04:40,543
[Rock music playing]

72
00:04:40,713 --> 00:04:42,408
Just come tonight.

73
00:04:43,883 --> 00:04:46,579
lsn't showing up the least you can do?

74
00:04:47,887 --> 00:04:51,948
Funny, l thought the same thing
about my dad my last 10 birthdays.

75
00:04:52,825 --> 00:04:55,225
JORDAN: Tru, l'm sorry, that's not--
TRU: For what?

76
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:59,129
For breaking up my parents' marriage,
or pretending it never happened?

77
00:04:59,198 --> 00:05:01,257
You know, l just remembered
l got to be somewhere.

78
00:05:01,367 --> 00:05:02,356
